<h2>View product reporting history</h2>

<p>Product history shows all past metric submissions, allowing you to track trends and review historical data.</p>

<h3>Accessing product history</h3>
<ol>
    <li>Navigate to <strong>Reporting → Operational reporting</strong></li>
    <li>Find your product in the list</li>
    <li>Click on the product name</li>
    <li>Click <strong>View History</strong> or go to the <strong>History</strong> tab</li>
</ol>

<h3>History view</h3>
<p>The history page displays:</p>
<ul>
    <li>All reporting periods for the product</li>
    <li>Submitted dates</li>
    <li>Metric values for each period</li>
    <li>Who submitted each period's data</li>
    <li>Status of each submission</li>
</ul>

<h3>Filtering history</h3>
<p>You can filter the history by:</p>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Date range:</strong> View specific time periods</li>
    <li><strong>Year:</strong> Focus on a particular year</li>
    <li><strong>Status:</strong> Filter by submission status</li>
</ul>

<h3>Understanding the data</h3>
<p>For each period, you can see:</p>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Reporting period:</strong> Month and year</li>
    <li><strong>Submitted date:</strong> When metrics were submitted</li>
    <li><strong>Submitted by:</strong> Who entered the data</li>
    <li><strong>Metric values:</strong> All submitted metrics</li>
    <li><strong>Changes:</strong> Differences from previous period (if visible)</li>
</ul>

<h3>Trends and patterns</h3>
<p>Use the history to:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Identify trends over time</li>
    <li>Compare periods</li>
    <li>Spot anomalies or unusual values</li>
    <li>Track improvements or declines</li>
    <li>Support reporting and analysis</li>
</ul>

<h3>Exporting data</h3>
<p>If available, you can export historical data for:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Further analysis in spreadsheets</li>
    <li>Creating custom reports</li>
    <li>Sharing with stakeholders</li>
    <li>Archiving</li>
</ul>

<h3>Period exclusions</h3>
<p>Note that some periods may be excluded from reporting. These won't appear in the history if:</p>
<ul>
    <li>The period was excluded at the system level</li>
    <li>Your business area was excluded for that period</li>
    <li>The product was excluded for that specific period</li>
</ul>

<h3>Best practices</h3>
<ul>
    <li>Regularly review history to spot trends</li>
    <li>Use history to validate current submissions</li>
    <li>Compare similar periods (e.g., same month last year)</li>
    <li>Document any significant changes or anomalies</li>
    <li>Keep historical context when submitting new metrics</li>
</ul>

